Within 60 days after the Department receives an application for services for an individual, the Secretary, on the basis of the application, shall:
Determine whether there is a reasonable likelihood that the individual:
Has developmental disability; or
Does not have developmental disability, but may be eligible for individual support services under subsection (c) of this section; and
If a positive determination is made under item (1)(i) or (ii) of this subsection:
Approve the application;
Determine the nature of the disability;
Determine the nature of services that the individual may require;
Determine the type of environment in which any needed services could be provided with the least restriction on the liberty of the individual;
Determine what types of evaluations, if any, the individual requires;
Inform the individual of these determinations; and
Inform the individual that these determinations are preliminary and may be subject to modification as a result of further evaluation.
